1.title: The Vampire Who Loved Korean Wave
1.plot: Prince Panyera Twilight Walakia Kunyaris Romania Blaratua Transylvania New Moon Tenios Bellanuci Breaking Dawn Draculu Oolala Eclipse Apadia of planet Vampyrutus takes his father's place as the 72,490th king of Vampyrutus. To celebrate, loyal servants Gabri Ratiss (a wizard who can hear all sounds) and Galilu Genius (the greatest mind in universe with an IQ of 790) provide him with a trip to Earth where he can watch a live performance of his beloved k-pop group, Girls Girls. Mukadil Kejua (bloodthirsty swordsman) at first objects, as the old king has banned Girls ...

2.title: Looking for the Lost Baba
2.plot: Separated from his bodyguards in a crash landing, Prince shortly winds up the victim in several serious vehicular street accidents.

3.title: TaeChiiTaeChiiOop's Secret
3.plot: Following a rescue from the hospital, Dong-yub strands the vampires in a bathhouse after snatching Prince's red diamond.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: To assuage their wrath, Shin hides Prince and his bodyguards from deathly vicious "vampire-hating" humans at the company building.

5.title: Kiss Kiss
5.plot: Prince, in all his 200 years of life, has been told he's the handsomest being in the universe, but on Earth his type is considered a bomb while his three ugly companions are the hotties all women crave.

6.title: Immortal Beloved
6.plot: It's Su-mi's birthday, but an early morning row with Shin sends him out drinking with the other vampires. While Girls Girls throws her a party, she tells the story about how she met manager Shin - uh, his father.

7.title: Multiple Blood Clots
7.plot: During a TV appearance in which ZE:A members are asked which female group they like the most, they name Girls Girls, and Woo-hee among them. This has her excited but angers Prince, so the other Vampires decide to take revenge for him. It turns out a ZE:A member has a secret girlfriend, which gets exposed from the Vampires' prank played on him. Elsewhere, Woo-hee is humiliated during an audition for an ad.

8.title: The Promise of the Millennium
8.plot: Mukadil catches a cold, which others figure to be flu that will surely kill him (as many over the age of 65 die from it - and he's 200 years old).

9.title: Brand New Experience
9.plot: Having stayed on Earth longer than expected, the Vampires' food supplies run out. In the midst of starvation, two experience first love.

10.title: Secrets of Santa Claus
10.plot: Coming upon a Santa Claus at a shopping mall (and subsequently told of his blood-sucking origins from Shin), the vampires return to the store to make their Christmas wishes known.

11.title: Vampire Jean Valjean
11.plot: In trying to join Woo-hee at the movies, Prince is confounded by the human need for money and angered by his lack of it - till he discovers Su-mi's purse.

12.title: What Comes Out from the Colon
12.plot: Since vampires normally don't defecate, Su-mi rightfully frets over ever again seeing the diamond from a diamond ring she borrowed that Prince accidentally swallowed.

13.title: Do You Know the Girl Behind Rabbit's Mask?
13.plot: Woo-bin falls in love again, this time with a girl (presumably) inside a rabbit costume. Meanwhile, Prince wrecks Min-kyung's life.

14.title: Get Rid of the Hoodie!
14.plot: As the hiring of Min-kyung changes the sleeping arrangements at SD Entertainment (much to Su-mi's displeasure), Prince aims to reveal Yoo-bi's ever-hidden face.

15.title: The Maid
15.plot: Su-mi's sweet effort to get out of making a huge pile of kimchi turns sour when the hired help to replace her turns out to be a beauty who leaves all the men agog.

16.title: Chaebol's Daughter
16.plot: The Vampires get hot, bothered and uncomfortable when they discover Dong-yub's stash of porno mags.

17.title: Fashion King
17.plot:

18.title: Dong-yub's Son
18.plot: Learning that Dong-yub has a son throws Su-mi for a loop.

19.title: Episode #1.19
19.plot:

20.title: I Love You, Dad
20.plot: As a faulty furnace leaves everyone miserably cold at SD Entertainment, Jong-hyeon winds up in Prince's disfavor after applying his genius intelligence in a café sweepstakes.

21.title: Bad Tree Root
21.plot: As Jong-hyeon helps Min-ah improve her poor spelling skills, Prince and his other men hold up in the bathroom where smartphone reception is best.

22.title: Doghole
22.plot: A visit from another vampire prompts Prince and his men to start packing secretively, with Jong-hyeon and Woo-bin regretting the planned departure.

23.title: Yoo-bi's Face
23.plot: The fall of Yoo-bi's hoodie reveals a side to her silent self no one expects.

24.title: Soulmate
24.plot: Min-ah's relationship with Jong-hyeon is shaken by a female visitor.

25.title: Command
25.plot: Prince can barely control his urge to rip out Soo-hyuk's throat when Soo-hyuk is selected over him to film a kissing scene with Woo-hee.

26.title: Chores
26.plot: Delivering a potted plant for the director turns into more of a chore than the vampires first thought it would be.

27.title: Musoyu
27.plot: The director's efforts to de-clutter everyone's lives (and cut costs) by encouraging the Buddhist state of Musoyu leaves others cold and in the dark.

28.title: Curse of the Red Moon
28.plot: A lunar eclipse approaches, which will throw the vampires into a state of uncontrollable bloodlust.

29.title: Happy Prince
29.plot: The vampires prove their abilities: Prince's to out-sing pop star Kwang-hee, Jong-hyeon's to remember minute details, Soo-hyuk's to do stunt work, and Woo-bin to make money with a photographer.

30.title: Protect the Boss
30.plot: After Kwang-hee's assault outside the studio, the need for a bodyguard becomes apparent, so Min-kyung seeks lessons from Soo-hyuk.
